/***********************************************************************

	NOTE: the ofx-dev flickrScraperSlideShow is only based on this code, just a
		  previous version without flickr api dependencies, more like webImgLoader..


  forum post at: http://www.openframeworks.cc/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1257

	JGL - Posted: Tue Nov 04, 2008 9:18 pm

	flickrScraperSlideShow is an application I created with oF "00573-Xcode-Fat-YCAM-WithGui". It queries Flickr for a keyword and then displays the resulting (up to 100) images in a slideshow format.

	It uses a blocking call for getting the results from Flickr using their REST API:

	http://www.flickr.com/services/api/request.rest.html

	It then uses a thread to download images from Flickr.com, while allowing the slideshow to continue.

	Any comments welcome.

	System design and assembly by Joel Gethin Lewis
	http://www.joelgethinlewis.com
	XML query and manipulation of Flickr API by Brian Balantine, Jesús Gollonet Bailén
	http://www.openframeworks.cc/forum/viewtopic.php?p=3578
	slideshow logic based upon work by prisonerjohn, Memo Akten, Theo Watson, Zachary Lieberman, otherside, arturo
	http://www.openframeworks.cc/forum/viewtopic.php?t=816
	thread and scraping, SimpleWebScraper by Jesús Gollonet Bailén, Zachary Lieberman, arturo
	http://www.openframeworks.cc/forum/viewtopic.php?p=6715
	based in turn on work on webImageLoader by Brian Balantine, Theo Watson, Zachary Lieberman, mantissa, Matt Parker
	http://www.openframeworks.cc/forum/viewtopic.php?t=562

	Full source and project (OSX) (40KB):

	http://www.joelgethinlewis.com/download/flickrScraperSlideShow.zip

	more at: http://www.openframeworks.cc/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1257

